1 on 22 august 2008, the court published its reasons for judgment in cruse v construction, forestry, mining and energy union [2008] fca 1267 ("the substantive judgment").
in the substantive judgment, the court held that mr fry, a delegate of the respondent union, breached ss 298sc and 170nc of the workplace relations act 1996 (cth) ("the wr act ").
